Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer II, Backend Full Stack - AI Platform* with *Rippling*. I bring over three years of professional experience building fullstack web applications, AI-first backend systems, and production-grade agentic platforms, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade fullstack and AI-first systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a multi-agent CRM platform in Python, LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI serving 10,000+ users, routing requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with tenant-aware access control and JWT propagation — a zero-to-one product where I contributed to both architecture design and day-to-day feature delivery. I simultaneously owned the full client-side and server-side stack, building a React Flow and TypeScript visual workflow platform backed by Temporal for durable execution, as well as a production-grade MCP server with FastMCP exposing 160+ LLM-callable backend actions, complete with Pydantic validation, OpenTelemetry instrumentation, and multi-tenant isolation. To answer product questions at scale, I built LlamaIndex-powered RAG agents over PostgreSQL pgvector, and wired GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with OpenTelemetry trace-based evals that gate every AI agent release before production. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot backed by PostgreSQL and Redis, handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — work that demanded cross-functional collaboration with infrastructure and product teams and gave me deep familiarity with AWS services including Step Functions, which I used to orchestrate 100K+ weekly production executions while eliminating Lambda timeouts. I also optimized PostgreSQL with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, exposing the improvements through interactive React visualizations for business stakeholders — delivering end-to-end fullstack impact across both layers. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities and drive impact across Rippling's AI Platform in fast feedback loops.

What draws me most to this role is the chance to build an AI-first product from the ground up, operating at the intersection of AI and UX that Rippling's AI Platform team is pioneering. I have always been passionate about *freeing smart people to work on hard problems* and pushing the limits of what software can automate — and I see Rippling's goal of giving businesses one place to manage every part of the employee lifecycle as one of the most ambitious expressions of that idea. The engineering culture of "never not my problem" also mirrors how I approach ownership: I do not hand off incomplete systems or wait for scope to be perfectly defined — I close the loop, write the tests, and ship. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

